text.tspan: 1) Fulfilling of the purchasing orders2) Maintaining the desired quality of service and products3) Timely delivery of the product / service.4) Maintain / provide adequate resources to provide the level of service required by our environmental protection standards.Any positive or adverse feedback will be recorded in the Phoenix system in the Vendor’s Register Feedback Section.A supplier who is unable to maintain a score of 70 or above in meeting the above standards shall be advised of his shortcomings andwill be given a chance to improve. If there is no improvement in performance then supplier / service shall be taken off the approved listof suppliers.Any supplier who has on more than one occasion been found adopting unethical practices or supplying inferior quality products orservices shall be reclassified as Class D.Brief details of the case and the case documents shall be uploaded in the Phoenix system in the Vendor’s Register Feedback Section.5.6STORES AND SPARES5.6.1PURCHASING PROCEDURE5.6.2ENVIRONMENTAL ASPECT OF PRODUCTSWhen placing orders for products the following shall be taken into consideration.1) The effect of the product or material on the environment.
